Temperature Conversion: Celsius to Fahrenheit

To convert a temperature from Celsius to Fahrenheit, use the formula:

￼

Where:
	•	￼ is the temperature in Fahrenheit.
	•	￼ is the temperature in Celsius.

Algorithm:
	1.	Start
	2.	Input: Read the temperature in Celsius (￼).
	3.	Process: Calculate the temperature in Fahrenheit using the formula:
	•	￼
	4.	Output: Display the temperature in Fahrenheit (￼).
	5.	End

Pseudocode:

BEGIN
    INPUT C  // Read temperature in Celsius
    F ← (C * 9/5) + 32  // Convert to Fahrenheit
    PRINT F  // Display temperature in Fahrenheit
END

